<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKW-NCAA-NOTEBOOK-LADN </SLUG>
 
CSUN's JERRO HAS WRITE STUFF 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ And how much have you slept, Cal State Northridge
coach Frozena Jerro, since learning your team will play Colorado
State in the NCAA Tournament?
</P>
<P>
   Answer: Hardly.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm up watching film all night,'' Jerro said. ``I probably
won't get much sleep tonight, either.''
</P>
<P>
   True, Jerro has spent a lot of time dissecting the Rams and
building a game plan. But she also has been discovered by the
national media, who want to know about the coach who took over
after the head coach was arrested and a second coach resigned
before coaching a game.
</P>
<P>
   USA Today interviewed her for an hour. The San Jose Mercury News
flew a reporter down to talk to her. The Colorado media,
understandably, is very interested, and some of the newspapers that
cover the Big Sky Conference told Northridge Sports Information
Director Ryan Finney they will cover Northridge in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Jerro also has spent plenty of time talking to newspapers and
radio stations from Montana, Arizona and Missouri.
</P>
<P>
   The late show: Ask players if they like the 9 p.m. PST starts
and most don't mind because they'll be on television. ESPN2 has the
Northridge game on Friday, and ESPN will televise UCLA on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Still, as UCLA's Marie Philman says, ``I've never played that
late of a game.''
</P>
<P>
   Only UCLA's Erica Gomez says she loves the late start.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not a morning basketball person,'' she said. ``It takes me
awhile to get my knees in shape.''
</P>
<P>
   Gomez also is used to playing late. In high school, she and her
older sister, Audrey, often went to local gymnasiums as late as
10:30 p.m. and shoot around.
</P>
<P>
   At midnight, they were still there.
</P>
<P>
   ``You go in and stay there, and time passes you by,'' Gomez's
father, Larry, said.
</P>
<P>
   Looking ahead: Tickets are on sale for the NCAA West Regional at
the Sports Arena on March 20-22. UCLA and Northridge will play
there if they win two games in their respective sub-regionals.
</P>
<P>
   A three-game ticket package is $30 for a reserved seat on the
lower level and $25 in the upper level. Youth packages are $12.
</P>
<P>
   Semifinals are March 20 at 7 and 9 p.m. The final is March 22 at
9 p.m., with the winner advancing to the Final Four in San Jose.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
