   BBO-ANDERSON-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column:
Before he was to throw out the first ball at Old-Timer's Day at
Yankee Stadium last July, silver-haired Joe DiMaggio suddenly
arrived in the shadowy corridor behind the Yankee dugout. He was
wearing what he often wore: a blue blazer over a white shirt with a
burgundy tie, sharply creased gray slacks and shiny black shoes.
``You look great,'' I told him. ``You can't see how I feel,'' he
said, smiling. By Dave Anderson.
