<P>
   VIETNAMESE DISHES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Vietnam's food is a happy result of bad times. This
swath of land between China and India has long been coveted by
outside forces. In earliest times, it was the Mongols from China
who came over the bordering mountains to exert their will. Later,
in this century, the French came colonizing, bringing Catholicism
and their system of government. In between, this verdant land of
earth and water was visited by Portuguese traders and Japanese
occupiers. This historic uproar has resulted in a cuisine that
incorporates elements from all these nations. By BEVERLY BUNDY.
Story will move in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
