<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ONE RACE, THREE DEAD HEATS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: At Trinity Meadows ractrack, there was once a triple dead
heat in each position. Who were the winners and what were the
payoffs?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.J., Azle, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: It sounds like you're referring to the ninth race at Trinity
Meadows on Jan. 5, 1996. In that race, two horses tied for first,
two for third, and two for fifth _ no winners were recorded for
second or fourth because of the ties.
</P>
<P>
   The American Quarter Horse Association is not aware of any other
three-tie races, representative Stacy Krug said.
</P>
<P>
   First-place payouts were for First Heartbeat ($3 to win, $3.20
to place and $3.40 to show) and Comntoaracetraknearu ($5 to win,
$5.20 to place and $3.20 to show). Third-place payouts won for Ima
Last Glass ($2.40 to show) and Tornado Touchdown ($3 to show).
</P>
<P>
   Fifth-place finishers J.J. Shot Glass and Dash On High ended up
out of the money.
</P>
<P>
   Trifecta winners earned $219.40 by picking both first-place
finishers and either of the third-place horses.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Whom can I contact about an oil painting of Sadie T. Beckham
from Texas Christian University in 1936?
</P>
<P>
   _ I.K., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Beckham, who died in 1955 at age 74, was a TCU trustee for 17
years and was the second woman voted to the board, said Terri
Gartner, administrative assistant in the TCU Office of
Communications.
</P>
<P>
   She began her TCU career as matron of Jarvis Hall and was
appointed dean of women in 1921, retiring from that position in
1937. The sorority house Beckham-Shelburne Hall is named after
Beckham and Elizabeth Shelburne, her successor as dean of women.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, contact Gartner at 257-7810.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to David Spade?
</P>
<P>
   _ C.D., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Spade in care of his agent, Adam Venit, at Endeavor,
9701 Wilshire Blvd., 10th Floor, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   Spade, who resides part of the year in his hometown of
Scottsdale, Ariz., bought a $3 million home in Beverly Hills in
February, according to the ``Los Angeles Times.''
</P>
<P>
   The 34-year-old comedian stars in ``Just Shoot Me'' and will be
appearing in the film ``Lost and Found,'' to be released in April.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
