   COLORADO-KOGOVSEK-SLOVENIA. Ray Kogovsek, the Denver lobbyist
who represented Colorado's 3rd District in Congress for six years,
just gained two million new constituents. That's because the
Slovenian parliament recently voted to approve Kogovsek's
appointment as the Balkan nation's honorary consul to Colorado, a
post that puts him in charge of representing Slovenia's interests
in the Centennial State (400 words). By Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT-SATELITE-NETWORKS. Congress is working on
legislation that would restore network programming to home
satellite dish owners such as Lisa Bazzano of Norfolk. Bazzano and
hundreds of thousands of satellite owners across the country lost
transmission of FOX and CBS after a federal court decision went
into effect two weeks ago (between 600 and 800 words). By Laura
Maggi
</P>
