   INDIANA-STEEL-BILL. A bill to limit steel imports was passed by
the House Ways and Means Committee Wednesday, but will almost
certainly be vetoed by President Clinton if it passes muster with
the full House (500 words). By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-RECESSION-READY. Maine is one of a handful of states that
could weather a recession without big spending cuts or higher
taxes, according to a new study that gives the state high marks for
fiscal discipline (600 words). By Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   NEVADA-SATELLITE-BRYAN. A Senate committee passed a bill
Wednesday that would allow about 75,000 Silver State satellite
television subscribers to receive local programming until the end
of the year (600 words). By Mark D. Preston
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-STEEL-COMMITTEE. A House committee on Wednesday allowed
tough steel legislation to move to the House floor, but recommended
the measure be defeated once it got there (approximately 300
words). By Sean Gorman
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-BALDWIN-FARM. Madison Democrat Tammy Baldwin's
legislation that would extend bankruptcy provisions for farmers six
months beyond their scheduled expiration on April 1 was expected to
pass through the House today. By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
