<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EBERT-CO-HOST-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THUMBS UP FOR ELVIS MITCHELL, EBERT'S NEXT GUEST HOST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ebert _ and Elvis?
</P>
<P>
   Star-Telegram film critic Elvis Mitchell is among the guest
hosts named to fill in for the late Gene Siskel on the movie-review
show that Siskel shared with Roger Ebert.
</P>
<P>
   Mitchell, who is also the longtime movie reviewer for National
Public Radio's ``Weekend Edition,'' will tape the show with Ebert
in Chicago next week. It will air at 10:45 p.m. March 14
</P>
<P>
   Tom Shales, who reviews television for The Washington Post and
movies for National Public Radio, has taped two programs with
Ebert. Joel Siegel, the movie critic for ABC-TV's ``Good Morning
America,'' has also agreed to do an episode.
</P>
<P>
   Shales, who taped two episodes before Siskel's death, has said
that he doesn't want to continue in the slot permanently.
</P>
<P>
   No co-host has been named for March 21. Although Siegel has been
confirmed as a fill-in, his air date has yet to be scheduled.
</P>
<P>
   No plans have been set to have Ebert do the show alone, the
spokeswoman said, because Buena Vista wants two reviewers.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's the format: two people debating about movies,'' the
spokeswoman said. ``Although in the past, Roger has done two shows
on his own. For scheduling reasons then, we were unable to have
someone else with him. But our goal is to have a series of guest
critics until the end of the season.''
</P>
<P>
   The season ends in August.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
