<P>
   He died Monday morning, only a few hours after the great
DiMaggio.
</P>
<P>
   There are moments when we can no longer ignore coincidence or
cliche.
</P>
<P>
   On his last day, I watched again from my father's room as clouds
gathered on the horizon, remembering the old saying he'd repeat in
the dugout when a sudden storm swept in, interrupting our game.
</P>
<P>
   `'That's baseball,'' he'd tell us. ``Sometimes you win.
Sometimes you lose. Sometimes _ it rains.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
E.J. Montini can be reached at ed.montini(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
