<P>
   AMGEN-PROSTATE-CANCER (Los Angeles) _ Amgen, the Thousand Oaks,
Calif., biotech giant, said Wednesday it has signed a $100 million
deal to help develop and market a drug to treat prostate cancer.
Because of increased sales of its three other drugs, the company
said it should still be on target for analysts' earnings estimates.
By Ben Sullivan.
