   VA-NY-TRASH (Sussex, Va.) _ In this quiet corner of southern
Virginia, the humans are few, the wildlife plentiful. But if the
county is rich in beauty, it has also been poor in resources. For
years, residents dumped their trash into the nearest hole in the
ground. No new schools had been built in 30 years. That was before
Sussex County discovered garbage. Five years ago, it embarked on a
controversial path that many people believed would improve their
struggling economy while jeopardizing their beloved environs:
accepting a private, state-of-the-art landfill that would import
thousands of tons of garbage a day, much of it from New York City.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 1,600 words.
(Eds.: Budgeted earlier as VA-NY-TRANSIT)
