<P>
   IOWA-POLLS (Washington) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush holds a
commanding lead among the likely candidates in next year's
important Iowa Republican presidential caucuses, a new poll shows.
Bush led former American Red Cross president Elizabeth Dole 32.7
percent to 14.7 percent in the Iowa survey. Former Vice President
Dan Quayle was third in the poll, with 7.3 percent. By CRAGG HINES.
(Already filed.)
