withdraws funding for a bilingual children's book published by a
small El Paso company after learning that the author is
Subcommander Marcos, head of the Zapatista guerrillas of southern
Mexico. The chairman of the endowment yanked funding for fear some
of the money might find its way to the rebels. By THADDEUS HERRICK.
(Already filed.)
