   LAWYERS-FRAUD (Kansas City, Kan.) _ A federal judge acquits two
lawyers of charges in a major Medicare fraud case. The case is of
particular interest to the legal and health-care community because
Ruth Lehr and Mark R. Thompson, both specialists in health-care
law, were the first lawyers in the country to have been charged in
a Medicare fraud case as a result of their legal work. By JOHN T.
DAUNER. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
