<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-BERLIN-REICHSTAG-NYT (moved on Friday, Mar. 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Mar. 5,
about the rebuilding of the Reichstag in Berlin referred
imprecisely to Germany's leadership at its completion. While
Bismarck was instrumental in the building's construction, he was no
longer Chancellor of Germany when it was completed in 1894.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DEATH-PENALTY-NYT (moved on Monday, Mar. 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Mar. 8,
about the movement opposing the death penalty movement misstated
the affiliation of Richard Dieter. He is executive director of the
Death Penalty Information Center, not the National Coalition to
Abolish the Death Penalty.
</P>
