<P>
   (NYT30) LONDON -- March 10, 1999 -- SUB-BRITISH-AUTHOR'S-MUSE,
3-10 -- Alex Garland knows literary success ``could slip away
easily.'' The author of two well-received novels, ``The Beach'' and
``The Tesseract,'' Garland, 28, builds his plots, he says, with
comic-strip storyboards in mind. ``I leave a lot of gaps, and in
order for the book to work, the reader needs to fill in those
gaps,'' he says. ``The reader needs to engage.'' (Jonathan
Player/New York Times Photo)
</P>
