<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-DOLE-POLITICS-NYT, which moved
in ``w'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``There's always a place at the table for a female candidate.
But for it to become more than that, she has to have a message
beyond, `I am woman, hear me roar.'''
</P>
<P>
   _ALEX CASTELLANOS, who has worked for Elizabeth Dole, on her
potential as a presidential candidate.
</P>
</TEXT>
