<P>
   (NYT20) FAIRFIELD, Calif. -- March 10, 1999 --
MILITARY-VACCINES, 3-10 -- Jeffrey Betendorf talks about his
reasons for refusing the Air Force's orders to receive an anthrax
vaccine in the backyard of his home on Wednesday. After threatening
him with court martial, the Air Force discharged him under ``other
than honorable conditions.'' Sixteen months after the Pentagon
announced that all 2.4 million military personnel, whether on
active duty or in the reserves or national guard, would be
vaccinated, the military is facing a rebellion from a small, but
growing legion of those who have refused. (Thor Swift/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) UNDATED -- March 10, 1999 -- SCI-ORGAN-TRANSPLANTS-2,
